# Memory — Galileyo Studios

## Now
- Active branch: `main` (studios work lands here; `development` is stale per branch audit)
- Studios routes and DB seed are in place; recent commits show nav polish, mobile layout fixes, episode roadmap grid, and lead-capture hardening
- Next likely focus: Phase 3 backend wiring (Stripe, Cloudflare Stream signed URLs, email automation) or Phase 4+ per `docs/studios-v2/`

## Project
- **Name**: Galileyo Studios (sub-brand inside Galileyo)
- **What it is**: A satellite-delivered information distribution platform (Galileyo) with a new Studios vertical for original short-form films. Studios lets users watch Episode 1 free after email signup, purchase Episodes 2-7 ($7 each) or unlock all via Bronze membership ($24/year), and become film/game producers ($50-$250K tiers). The Studios section lives inside the main Next.js app at `/studios/*` and uses a cinematic dark gold theme layered on top of the main app's cyan/blue design tokens.
- **Stack**: Next.js 15 (App Router, turbopack), React 19, TypeScript strict, tRPC v11, Drizzle ORM + MySQL, Better Auth, Tailwind, shadcn/ui (`@galileyo/ui`), Expo SDK 53 (React Native + NativeWind), Redis pub/sub, PM2 (4 processes in prod), Turborepo + pnpm workspaces, PostHog analytics, `motion@^12` for animation
- **Repo / Production**: `main` branch is the integration target; staging at `next.galileyo` (confirm exact deploy mechanism with Brett Miller)

## Key Paths
- `apps/nextjs/src/app/(app)/studios/` — all Studios route pages (layout, page, episodes/[slug], watch/[slug], producers, membership, sponsors, affiliates, about, donate, thank-you)
- `apps/nextjs/src/components/studios/` — Studios-specific components (StudiosShell, EpisodeCard, WatchPlayer, etc.)
- `packages/api/src/router/studios.ts` — Studios tRPC router (PLURAL; `studio.ts` singular is the creator analytics router — DO NOT confuse them)
- `packages/db/src/schema/` — Drizzle schema; Studios tables: `studios_episode`, `studios_email_signup`, `studios_access_grant`, `studios_bronze_subscription`, `studios_producer`, `studios_lead`
- `apps/nextjs/src/components/video/video-player.tsx` — existing HLS player (851 lines); Studios uses a dedicated `StudiosFilmPlayer` wrapping hls.js, not this shared component
- `apps/nextjs/src/server/trpc-ws.ts` — WebSocket server (separate PM2 process from Next.js)
- `apps/nextjs/src/env/` — env validation via `@t3-oss/env`; new vars must also be added to `turbo.json` globalEnv array
- `packages/api/src/router/` — all tRPC routers; `root.ts` composes `appRouter`
- `packages/db/src/schema.ts` — main schema file; no migrations folder (uses `db:push` workflow)
- `docs/studios-v2/GALILEYO_STUDIOS_V2_MASTER_BLUEPRINT.md` — authoritative Studios spec (read before any Studios work)

