- Naming constraint: `packages/api/src/router/studios.ts` (plural) vs `studio.ts` (singular, creator analytics) -- never mix them

## Recommended Skills (global, in ~/.claude/skills)
- `implement` — primary skill for building out Phase 3 tRPC routers, Stripe routes, and email templates
- `tdd` — engine-layer logic (access grants, token signing) should be unit-tested before wiring to routes
- `review` — before any Stripe or access-check code ships; security-sensitive flows deserve a dedicated review pass
- `prototype` — useful for mocking Studios checkout UI before Stripe credentials arrive from Brett Miller
- `email` — Studios requires 4 new React Email templates (welcome, purchase receipt, Bronze welcome, producer welcome)
- `scaffold-exercises` — generating typed stubs for the remaining Studios tRPC procedures and Drizzle queries
- `diagnosing-bugs` — resilient lead-insert and nav-lurch commits suggest prod edge cases still surfacing

## Patterns Noticed
- No migrations folder: schema changes go via `pnpm db:push` (Drizzle push workflow), not generate/migrate
- Every app wraps scripts with `with-env` (dotenv from root `.env`); new env vars need registration in `turbo.json` globalEnv
- `timingMiddleware` injects 100-500ms artificial delay in dev to surface waterfalls; do not mistake for real latency
- Studios theme scoped via `.studios-theme` CSS class on the layout wrapper, not global; leaves the rest of the app untouched
- Import aliases: `~/` for app-local paths, `@galileyo/*` for monorepo packages
- No em dashes anywhere in copy or code comments (house rule; use commas, parens, or separate sentences)
- All paid/gated routes require server-side auth checks in server components; client-only gating is not acceptable
